# Mote Project

Raspberry Pi 4 touchscreen remote-desktop appliance (7" 800x480 display).

## Target Platform

- **OS**: Raspberry Pi OS based on **Debian Trixie** (NOT Bookworm)
- **Display**: Wayland (Sway compositor) — NO X11 on either device
- **RDP client**: `freerdp3-sdl` (binary `sdl-freerdp3`) — the SDL client replaced the deprecated `wlfreerdp3` Wayland client as of FreeRDP 3.0

## Remote Host

- Runs **KRDP** (KDE RDP server), port 3389, NLA auth
- NOT krfb, NOT x11vnc, NOT xrdp

## First-Time Accuracy

- Research package names, binary paths, and API details BEFORE writing code
- Verify against the actual target distro (Trixie), not Bookworm or generic Debian
- When unsure, check the real package file list (e.g. packages.debian.org filelist) to confirm binary names
- Do not guess — look it up. Getting it wrong wastes a build-deploy cycle on a Pi
- Always read the actual man page for command syntax before writing commands (e.g. FreeRDP3 uses /cert:ignore not /cert-ignore)
- Ask clarifying questions up front rather than assuming
